386→                        <div id="content">For every $x\in\mathbb{R}$ let $A_x\subset \mathbb{R}$ be a bounded set with outer measure $&#60;1$. Must there exist an infinite independent set, that is, some infinite $X\subseteq \mathbb{R}$ such that $x\not\in A_y$ for all $x\neq y\in X$?<br><br>If the sets $A_x$ are closed and have measure $&#60;1$, then must there exist an independent set of size $3$?</div>
